Package org.semanticweb.vlog4j.core.model.api

Interface DatatypeConstant

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Constant, Entity, Term
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DatatypeConstantImpl
    public interface DatatypeConstant
extends Constant
    Interface for datatype constants, i.e. for constants that represent a specific value of a concrete datatype). Such terms are of type TermType.DATATYPE_CONSTANT. Note that datatype literal is a common name of the representation of specific values for a datatype. We mostly avoid this meaning of literal since a literal in logic is typically a negated or non-negated atom.
    Author:
    Markus Kroetzsch

      • getLexicalValue

        String getLexicalValue()
        Returns the lexical value of the data value, i.e. a string that encodes a specific value based on the value's datatype. Note that there can be several strings that represent the same value, depending on the rules of the datatype, and that there the value used here does not have to be a canonical representation.
        Returns:
        a non-null string
